OL,7,FHe took #85 cash from the till and
OL,8,Floaded a bag with over #1,000 worth of
OL,9,Ftobacco and e-cigarettes before
OL,10,Ffleeing the scene.
OL,12,FLi, of Rhostyllen, appeared before
OL,13,FMold Crown Court today on Thursday, 5
OL,14,FSeptember for sentencing, having
OL,15,Fadmitted a charge of robbery at a
OL,16,Fprevious hearing.
OL,18,FHe was jailed for three years and nine
OL,19,Fmonths. The second person involved in
OL,20,Fthe robbery remains unidentified.
